</h1>\r\n<p class=\"text-center\">\r\n<img src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/aya-product-1.png\" alt=\"aya-product-1\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-730\" />\r\n</p>\r\n<h2>Simple, honest, clean plantbutters</h2>\r\nOur plantbutters are simple, honest and clean, here\'s how:\r\n<h3>SIMPLE</h3>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\">Our plantbutters were dreamed up in Amy\'s home kitchen using domestic equipment and organic ingredients. Amy\'s motivation was to create a <b>delicious tasting, plantbased alternative to dairy butter</b> because plantbutter <a href=\"http://www.conservationmagazine.org/2014/03/butter-vs-margarine-environmental/\"><b>has a four times lower carbon footprint than dairy butter</b></a> and has no association with animal cruelty often linked to the conventional dairy industry.</p>\r\n<h3>HONEST</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"aya-emphasis-list\">\r\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">SINCERE</span> - We will <b>always provide you with information</b> about what our products contain, how they are made and where the ingredients are sourced.</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">SUSTAINABLE</span> - We are a sustainable business that ensures that all activities related to our business <b>consider the impact it has on the environment</b> and the ability of future generations to meet their own needs.\r\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">CONSCIOUS BUSINESS</span> - We believe that our business should align with your highest values so that <b>when you choose our products you are doing the greatest good for the earth and all its beings</b>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>CLEAN</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"aya-emphasis-list\">\r\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">NO HEXANE</span> - We use only organic ingredients which means our ingredients are <b>grown with natural, organic fertilisers and pesticides and do not undergo any toxic processing</b>. Our plant oils have been extracted without solvents unlike un-organic oils which use Hexane, a petroleum derivative, to extract non-organic oils from their seeds.</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">NO PALM-OIL</span> - We <b>prefer cocoa butter</b> which is naturally firm at room temperature and which gives our plantbutters their unique melt-in-the-mouth quality just like dairy butter.</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">NO GMO</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">NO DAIRY</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">NO GLUTEN</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">NO PLASTIC</span> - We package our plantbutters in <b>compostable packaging</b> and we will never use plastic.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Who is Aya</h2>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\"><b>Aya is a west African Goddess of forests, she protects the forest and its animals and she teaches her tribe how to use the plants to sustain and heal themselves. We chose the name Aya because we align with her values.</b></p>\r\n<p class=\"text-center\">\r\n<img src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/aya-forest.jpg\" alt=\"aya-forest\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-562\" />\r\n</p>\r\n','Home','','publish','closed','closed','','aya-home','','','2018-09-20 16:34:56','2018-09-20 16:34:56','',0,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/?page_id=287',0,'page','',0),(288,1,'2017-10-24 16:54:12','2017-10-24 16:54:12','','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','287-revision-v1','','','2017-10-24 16:54:12','2017-10-24 16:54:12','',287,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/287-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(289,1,'2017-10-24 17:04:50','2017-10-24 17:04:50','','Articles','','publish','closed','closed','','aya-articles','','','2018-09-03 15:15:26','2018-09-03 15:15:26','',0,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/?page_id=289',0,'page','',0),(290,1,'2017-10-24 17:04:51','2017-10-24 17:04:51','','Aya Articles','','inherit','closed','closed','','289-revision-v1','','','2017-10-24 17:04:51','2017-10-24 17:04:51','',289,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/289-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(291,1,'2017-10-25 14:33:30','2017-10-25 14:33:30','  <section className=\"section-color-blue\">\r\n            <h2>What is Aya?</h2>\r\n            <p className=\"intro-1\">\r\n            Butta is a plant based replacement for dairy butter and can be used for spreading, cooking and baking.  Butta looks and tastes like dairy butter.  It has a fat content of 75% similar to dairy butter but unlike dairy butter Butta contains 45% saturated, 15% mono-saturated and 18% poly-unsaturated fats making it a healthier choice.</p>\r\n            <p className=\"intro-1\">\r\n            Butta differentiates itself from other margarines by offering an organic margarine spread that contains no mono- and diglycerides of fatty acids (trans-fat) or palm oil.  It uses plant milk, not water and its core oils are coconut oil and cocoa butter.  Butta is packaged in greaseproof paper with a cardboard sleeve and uses no plastic packaging.</p>\r\n            <dl>\r\n                <dt>Butta ingredients:</dt>\r\n                <dd><span className=\"fa-stack fa-md\"><i className=\"fa fa-check fa-stack-2x\"></i></span><span className=\"dd\">GMO (genetically modified organics) free</span></dd>\r\n                <dd><span className=\"fa-stack fa-md\"><i className=\"fa fa-check fa-stack-2x\"></i></span><span className=\"dd\">Dairy free</span></dd>\r\n                <dd><span className=\"fa-stack fa-md\"><i className=\"fa fa-check fa-stack-2x\"></i></span><span className=\"dd\">Lactose free</span></dd>\r\n                <dd><span className=\"fa-stack fa-md\"><i className=\"fa fa-check fa-stack-2x\"></i></span><span className=\"dd\">Gluten free</span></dd>\r\n                <dd><span className=\"fa-stack fa-md\"><i className=\"fa fa-check fa-stack-2x\"></i></span><span className=\"dd\">Palm oil free</span></dd>\r\n                <dd><span className=\"fa-stack fa-md\"><i className=\"fa fa-check fa-stack-2x\"></i></span><span className=\"dd\">No Hexane</span></dd>\r\n                <dd><span className=\"fa-stack fa-md\"><i className=\"fa fa-check fa-stack-2x\"></i></span><span className=\"dd\">No trans or hydrogenated fat</span></dd>\r\n            </dl>\r\n          </section>\r\n\r\n          <parallax image=\"Butta-wooden-table.jpeg\">\r\n            <h2>Butta an alternative for spreading, cook and baking</h2>\r\n          </parallax>\r\n          <section className=\"section-color-purple intro-list\">\r\n            <h2 className=\"\">Why will consumers buy Butta?</h2>\r\n            <p className=\"intro intro-3\"><span className=\"fa-stack fa-lg\"><i className=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o fa-stack-2x\"></i></span><em className=\"pullout-super\">The move to plant based alternatives is one of the fastest growing lifestyles in the world.</em></p>\r\n           <p><a href=\"https://www.vegansociety.com/whats-new/news/find-out-how-many-vegans-are-great-britain\">A study by Ipsos MORI in 2016</a> reveals that there are at least 542,000 vegans (a person who does not eat or use animal products) in Britain, three and a half times as many as there was in 2006.</p>\r\n            <p><a href=\"http://ucfoodobserver.com/2015/06/04/report-un-urges-global-move-to-meat-and-dairy-free-diet/\">United Nations Environment Programme</a> highlighted the strain of agricultural products on the environment back in 2010.  Consumers are becoming increasingly aware that a switch to plant based foods is required to cut gas greenhouse emissions and sustain the ever increasing population.</p>\r\n            <p><a href=\"https://thinkprogress.org/the-netherlands-new-dietary-guidelines-take-meat-off-the-menu-a97c40f05d84#.qqjmqqj68\">New dietary guidelines</a> for the Netherlands, the UK and the US take into account the environmental impact when formulating dietary recommendations promoting plant based-foods over agricultural products.</p>\r\n\r\n            <p className=\"intro intro-3\"><span className=\"fa-stack fa-lg\"><i className=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o fa-stack-2x\"></i></span><em className=\"pullout-super \">Consumers are choosing foods that contain natural ingredients over \'non-fat\' and \'low-fat\' varieties because they are seen as a more wholesome and healthier choice.</em></p>\r\n            <p><a href=\"http://www.alternet.org/food/how-low-fat-foods-actually-made-america-fat\">How low-fat foods actually made America fat</a></p>\r\n            <p>An article <a href=\"https://blendle.com/i/wsj-com/will-margarine-become-toast-at-unilever/bnl-wsj-20160119-SB12115899085733003306504581487633666776002?sharer=eyJ2ZXJzaW9uIjoiMSIsInVpZCI6ImFteW12YXJnYSIsIml0ZW1faWQiOiJibmwtd3NqLTIwMTYwMTE5LVNCMTIxMTU4OTkwODU3MzMwMDMzMDY1MDQ1ODE0ODc2MzM2NjY3NzYwMDIifQ%3D%3D\">in The Wallstreet Journal</a> reports butter\'s resurgence over margarine (2016)</p>\r\n            <p className=\"intro intro-3\"><span className=\"fa-stack fa-lg\"><i className=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o fa-stack-2x\"></i></span><em className=\"pullout-super\">Consumers are making product choices based on the overall impact of the product on the environment most importantly, sustainability.</em></p>\r\n            <p>One of Butta\'s core values is to source ingredients from ethical and sustainable suppliers.</p>\r\n            <p>The European Margarine Association highlights the importance of sustainability <a href=\"http://imace.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/IMACE_Newsletter_lay-out-A4_MAI_v4.pdf\">as a key concept for society, business and policy makers</a>.</p>\r\n            <p><a href=\"http://www.baltimoresun.com/business/bs-bz-supermarket-sustainable-food-trend-20170127-story.html\">Giant Food introduces a ratings system </a>that measures the sustainability of food.</p>\r\n        </section>\r\n        <parallax image=\"Cocoa-beans.jpeg\">\r\n            <h2>Plant based food product sales topped $4.9B in 2016, growing 3.4% since 2015 </h2>\r\n\r\n        </parallax>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.spins.com/plant-based-foods-webinar/\">Spins Plant Based Foods Growth Opportunities in Retail</a>\r\n        <section className=\"section-color-blue intro-list\">\r\n            <h2 className=\"\">Why will retailers choose Butta</h2>\r\n            <p className=\"intro intro-3\"><span className=\"fa-stack fa-lg\"><i className=\"fa fa-gbp fa-stack-2x\"></i></span><em className=\"pullout-super \">Sales of plant based foods have outperformed all expectations</em></p>\r\n            <p>Sainsbury\'s vegan cheeses <a href=\"http://www.sainsburysmagazine.co.uk/blog/item/10-things-you-need-to-know-about-going-vegan\">outperformed projected sales targets by 300%</a></p>\r\n            <p>Zizzi restaurants <a href=\"https://www.thecaterer.com/articles/495103/zizzi-reports-150-increase-in-vegan-dish-sales\">reported a 150% increase in vegan dish sales.</a></p>\r\n            <p><a href=\"http://www.tidefordorganics.com/\">Tide Ford Organics</a> have revamped their range to be completely vegan.</p>\r\n            <p><a href=\"https://www.pret.co.uk/en-gb/little-veggie-pop-up\">Pret\'s Veggie Store</a> is so popular it is here to stay.</p>\r\n            <p>Even <a href=\"http://www.benjerry.com/flavors/non-dairy\">Ben and Jerry\'s</a> has a non-dairy flavours.</p>\r\n            <p>67% of consumers in the US choose plant based milks because they like the taste of it and 65% of consumers choose plant based milks because it\'s healthier than dairy.</p>\r\n            <p className=\"intro intro-3\"><span className=\"fa-stack fa-lg\"><i className=\"fa fa-gbp fa-stack-2x\"></i></span><em className=\"pullout-super\">As margarine sales flatten, Butta offers a plant based alternative that not only looks, tastes and behaves like dairy butter but offers all the benefits of plant based oils.</em></p>\r\n            <p>Retail butter compound annual growth rate (CAGR) forecast for 2015-2020 is 0.4% compared with margarine\'s -0.6%.  Butta bridges the gap between the popularity of plant based foods and the resurgence in butter sales.</p>\r\n        </section>\r\n        <parallax image=\"Girl-loves-cow.jpeg\">\r\n            <h2>Vegans are inspired by health, the environment and animal welfare</h2>\r\n        </parallax>\r\n        <section className=\"section-color-blue intro-list\">\r\n            <h2 className=\"\">Who is the target market for Butta</h2>\r\n            <p className=\"intro intro-3\"><span className=\"fa-stack fa-lg\"><i className=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o fa-stack-2x\"></i></span><em className=\"pullout-super \">Millenials (born between 1977 and 2000)</em></p>\r\n            <p><a href=\"https://www.vegansociety.com/whats-new/news/find-out-how-many-vegans-are-great-britain\">A study by Ipsos MORI in 2016</a>reveals that 42% of all vegans in the UK are between the ages of 18 and 34.</p>\r\n            <p><a href=\"http://www.spins.com/plant-based-foods-webinar/\">Spins Plant Based Foods Growth Opportunities in Retail</a> reports that in the US 1 in 10 millenials (born between 1977 and 2000) are vegan and vegetarian.</p>\r\n            <p className=\"intro intro-3\"><span className=\"fa-stack fa-lg\"><i className=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o fa-stack-2x\"></i></span><em className=\"pullout-super \">Living in urban and suburban areas</em></p>\r\n            <p>In the UK 82% of all vegans live in urban and suburban areas and London contains 22% of all vegans.</p>\r\n<p className=\"intro intro-3\"><span className=\"fa-stack fa-lg\"><i className=\"fa fa-lightbulb-o fa-stack-2x\"></i></span><em className=\"pullout-super \">Inspired to make vegan or vegetarian choices because of animal welfare, the environment or health</em></p>\r\n            <p><a href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/global/2016/sep/11/why-so-many-people-are-converting-to-veganism\">The Guardian</a> recently profiled 4 vegans and their motivation for converting to veganism</p>\r\n        </section>\r\n          <section className=\"section-color-red\">\r\n            <h2>What makes Butta healthy?</h2>\r\n            <div className=\"row\">\r\n              <div className=\"col-md-4\">\r\n                <div className=\"promo\">\r\n                  <div className=\"promo-image-wrapper\">\r\n                    <img src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/cocoanut.png\" width=\"138\" height=\"89\" className=\"image-center\" />\r\n                  </div>\r\n                  <h4>Coconut oil (28%)</h4>\r\n                  <p>Coconut oil is <em className=\"pullout \">good for cholesterol</em>, its high Lauric acid content means that its energy is absorbed quickly giving a <em className=\"pullout \">satisfying</em> feeling of fullness. It also has <em className=\"pullout \">antimicrobial</em> properties which fight viruses and bacterial infections.</p>\r\n                </div>\r\n              </div>\r\n              <div className=\"col-md-4\">\r\n                <div className=\"promo\">\r\n                  <div className=\"promo-image-wrapper\">\r\n                    <img src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/canola.png\" height=\"89\" className=\"image-center\" />\r\n                  </div>\r\n                  <h4>Canola oil (26%)</h4>\r\n                  <p>Canola oil has the <em className=\"pullout \">lowest saturated fat</em> content of all plant oils. Its beneficial high mono-unsaturated fat content protects our heart by maintaining good cholesterol levels and it contains both <em className=\"pullout \">omega-3</em> and <em className=\"pullout \">omega-6</em> essential fatty acids.</p>\r\n                </div>\r\n              </div>\r\n              <div className=\"col-md-4\">\r\n                <div className=\"promo\">\r\n                  <div className=\"promo-image-wrapper\">\r\n                    <img src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/cocoa.png\" width=\"138\" height=\"89\" className=\"image-center\" />\r\n                  </div>\r\n                  <h4>Cocoa butter (21%)</h4>\r\n                  <p>Cocoa butter is an excellent source of natural <em className=\"pullout \">anti-oxidants</em>, omega-3 and omega-6 essential fatty acids as well as nutrients that enhance the mood and <em className=\"pullout \">immune system</em>.</p>\r\n                </div>\r\n              </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n          </section>','About Butta','','inherit','closed','closed','','146-revision-v1','','','2017-10-25 14:33:30','2017-10-25 14:33:30','',146,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/146-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(292,1,'2017-10-25 14:34:11','2017-10-25 14:34:11','','Homely','','inherit','closed','closed','','287-revision-v1','','','2017-10-25 14:34:11','2017-10-25 14:34:11','',287,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/287-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(293,1,'2017-10-25 14:36:04','2017-10-25 14:36:04','Welcome to Aya. We believe that living plant-strong is similar to a future dominated by clean, renewable energy. We invite you to #jointheAYAlution and help us in our mission to reduce animal agriculture.\r\n\r\nAya is an African goddess of forests, animals and herbal healing. Inspired by her, our plantbutter is kinder to the animals, the earth and ourselves (Aya Original contains 10% less fat than cow\'s butter and 9% less saturated fat).','Homely','','inherit','closed','closed','','287-revision-v1','','','2017-10-25 14:36:04','2017-10-25 14:36:04','',287,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/287-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(294,1,'2018-09-20 16:34:39','2018-09-20 16:34:39','<h1 class=\"visible-xs-block\">Home</h1>\n<p class=\"text-center\">\n\n</p>\n<h2>Simple, honest, clean plantbutters</h2>\nOur plantbutters are simple, honest and clean, here\'s how:\n<h3>SIMPLE</h3>\n<p class=\"text-justify\">Our plantbutters were dreamed up in Amy\'s home kitchen using domestic equipment and organic ingredients. Amy\'s motivation was to create a <b>delicious tasting, plantbased alternative to dairy butter</b> because plantbutter <a href=\"http://www.conservationmagazine.org/2014/03/butter-vs-margarine-environmental/\"><b>has a four times lower carbon footprint than dairy butter</b></a> and has no association with animal cruelty often linked to the conventional dairy industry.</p>\n<h3>HONEST</h3>\n<ul class=\"aya-emphasis-list\">\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">SINCERE</span> - We will <b>always provide you with information</b> about what our products contain, how they are made and where the ingredients are sourced.</li>\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">SUSTAINABLE</span> - We are a sustainable business that ensures that all activities related to our business <b>consider the impact it has on the environment</b> and the ability of future generations to meet their own needs.\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">CONSCIOUS BUSINESS</span> - We believe that our business should align with your highest values so that <b>when you choose our products you are doing the greatest good for the earth and all its beings</b>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>CLEAN</h3>\n<ul class=\"aya-emphasis-list\">\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">NO HEXANE</span> - We use only organic ingredients which means our ingredients are <b>grown with natural, organic fertilisers and pesticides and do not undergo any toxic processing</b>. Our plant oils have been extracted without solvents unlike un-organic oils which use Hexane, a petroleum derivative, to extract non-organic oils from their seeds.</li>\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">NO PALM-OIL</span> - We <b>prefer cocoa butter</b> which is naturally firm at room temperature and which gives our plantbutters their unique melt-in-the-mouth quality just like dairy butter.</li>\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">NO GMO</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">NO DAIRY</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">NO GLUTEN</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">NO PLASTIC</span> - We package our plantbutters in <b>compostable packaging</b> and we will never use plastic.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Who is Aya</h2>\n<p class=\"text-justify\"><b>Aya is a west African Goddess of forests, she protects the forest and its animals and she teaches her tribe how to use the plants to sustain and heal themselves. We chose the name Aya because we align with her values.</b></p>\n<p class=\"text-center\">\n<img src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/aya-forest.jpg\" alt=\"aya-forest\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-562\" />\n</p>\n','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','287-autosave-v1','','','2018-09-20 16:34:39','2018-09-20 16:34:39','',287,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/287-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(295,1,'2017-10-25 14:38:00','2017-10-25 14:38:00','Welcome to Aya. We believe that living plant-strong is similar to a future dominated by clean, renewable energy. We invite you to #jointheAYAlution and help us in our mission to reduce animal agriculture.\r\n\r\nAya is an African goddess of forests, animals and herbal healing. Inspired by her, our organic plantbutter is kinder to the animals, the earth and ourselves (Aya Original contains 10% less fat than cow\'s butter and 9% less saturated fat).','Homely','','inherit','closed','closed','','287-revision-v1','','','2017-10-25 14:38:00','2017-10-25 14:38:00','',287,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/287-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(296,1,'2017-10-25 14:39:20','2017-10-25 14:39:20','Welcome to Aya. We believe that living plant-strong is similar to a future dominated by clean, renewable energy. We invite you to #jointheAYAlution and help us in our mission to reduce animal agriculture.\r\n\r\nAya is an African goddess of forests, animals and herbal healing. Inspired by her, our organic plantbutter is kinder to the animals, the earth and ourselves (Aya Original contains 10% less fat than cow\'s butter and 9% less saturated fat).','AYA','','inherit','closed','closed','','287-revision-v1','','','2017-10-25 14:39:20','2017-10-25 14:39:20','',287,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/287-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(297,1,'2017-10-25 14:44:07','2017-10-25 14:44:07','<h1 class=\"visible-xs-block\">Our Story</h1>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"text-center\">\r\n<img src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/aya-product-3.png\" alt=\"aya-product-3\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-728\" />\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>A kinder option</h2>\r\n<p class=\"justify\">The popularity of <span class=\"emphasis\">plantbased</span> foods cannot be denied and the reasons are simple; plantbased foods offer healthier options, have a far lighter tread on the environment and ensure no animal cruelty.  I started Aya because I wanted to offer you the option to choose a purely plantbased alternative to cow\'s butter and other vegetable based oil spreads which is just as tasty and just as versatile - now you can choose a kinder option whenever you like.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote class=\"inline-quote\">\r\n<p class=\"blockquote\">The more we grow and make an impact the more we will be able to make demands that align with our highest values but we will need your loyalty to get there.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<h2>Our values and ethics</h2>\r\nAya is far more than plantbased; our values and ethics extend to everything we do.  As a start:\r\n<ul class=\"ayaList\">\r\n<li>We prioritise <span class=\"emphasis\">sustainability</span> which means that we will always consider the impact of our activities on the the environment:</li>\r\n<li>We prioritise <span class=\"emphasis\">transparency</span> which means we believe that you have a right to know exactly what you are buying and how our business operates:</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>We will always provide you with information about what our products contain, how they are made and where the ingredients are sourced.</li>\r\n<li>We will always warn you of any health risks associated with our products.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li>We prioritise <span class=\"emphasis\">ethical trade</span> and adhere to the Ethical Trade Initiative Basic Code, United Nations Declaration of Human Rights and the International Labour Organisation Core Conventions.</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>We will always provide a fair livelihood for all our employees.  We believe that an individual\'s work should offer in return a sustainable and fair livelihood as well as job satisfaction.  We understand that the role of work is only one aspect of an individual\'s life and that happiness can only be achieved in a holistic and balanced way of living.\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"justify\">As a start-up we realise the importance of creating a profitable business that aligns with our core values.  We must be profitable so that we can pay our employees, provide a comfortable and conducive working environment and pay our investors a fair return on their investment.  Sometimes we may have to make a small compromise on our values but we will always do so with openness and inform you of our decision.  We will then consistently reassess our decisions in a timely manner.</p> \r\n\r\n<h3>This is what we have implemented so far:</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"ayaList\">\r\n<li>We only use <span class=\"emphasis\">non-GMO, organic ingredients</span> because we believe that food should be natural and we do not advocate any chemicals used in the growing, cultivation or processing of our ingredients</li>\r\n<li>We choose <span class=\"emphasis\">no palm-oil</span> because of the <a href=\"https://youtu.be/TQQXstNh45g\">catastrophic effects that palm-oil cultivation has had on our rain forests and their inhabitants</a></li>\r\n<li>We will never use plastic, we choose to <span class=\"emphasis\">package our plantbutters in compostable greaseproof paper</span> because this has the lowest environmental impact.  We encourage butter dishes as a way of preserving your butter in the fridge.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>And this is what we intend to implement as soon as we possibly can:</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"ayaList\">\r\n<li>We will be a <a href=\"https://bcorporation.net/\">Certified B Corporation</a>.  Certified B Corporations meet the highest standards of verified social and environmental performance, transparency and accountability. B Corporations are people using business as a force of good.</li>\r\n<li>We will be both <a href=\"https://www.soilassociation.org/\">Soil Association Organic</a> and <a href=\"https://www.vegansociety.com/\">The Vegan Society</a> accredited.</li>\r\n<li>We will use <a href=\"https://www.fairtrade.org.uk/\">Fairtrade Foundation</a> ingredients whenever we can.  Fairtrade is about better prices, decent working conditions, local sustainability and fair terms of trade for farmers and workers in the developing world. It requires companies to pay sustainable prices (which must never fall lower than the market price).</li>\r\n</ul>','Our story','','publish','closed','closed','','aya-about','','','2018-09-20 16:31:15','2018-09-20 16:31:15','',0,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/?page_id=297',0,'page','',0),(298,1,'2017-10-25 14:44:07','2017-10-25 14:44:07','','About Aya','','inherit','closed','closed','','297-revision-v1','','','2017-10-25 14:44:07','2017-10-25 14:44:07','',297,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/297-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(299,1,'2017-10-25 14:44:27','2017-10-25 14:44:27','  <section className=\"section-color-blue\">\r\n            <h2>What is Aya?</h2>\r\n            <p className=\"intro-1\">\r\n            Butta is a plant based replacement for dairy butter and can be used for spreading, cooking and baking.  Butta looks and tastes like dairy butter.  It has a fat content of 75% similar to dairy butter but unlike dairy butter Butta contains 45% saturated, 15% mono-saturated and 18% poly-unsaturated fats making it a healthier choice.</p>\r\n            <p className=\"intro-1\">\r\n            Butta differentiates itself from other margarines by offering an organic margarine spread that contains no mono- and diglycerides of fatty acids (trans-fat) or palm oil.  It uses plant milk, not water and its core oils are coconut oil and cocoa butter.  Butta is packaged in greaseproof paper with a cardboard sleeve and uses no plastic packaging.</p>\r\n  