sed to new¬†information and defensive about my¬†opinions.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">That\'s why I¬†believe that eating consciously is more important.¬† It\'s not about making judgements or identifications, its about doing what is right for the greater good.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"p3\"><span class=\"s1\">In every truth the opposite is equally true.¬†</span><span class=\"s2\">That is to say, any truth can only be expressed and put into words when it is one-sided. Everything that can be thought with the mind and said with words is one-sided, it\'s all just the half of it, lacking completeness, roundness, or unity.</span></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"p3\"><span class=\"s2\">Siddhartha by Hermann Hesse</span></p>','Nothing is black or white','','inherit','closed','closed','','131-revision-v1','','','2017-10-27 17:27:20','2017-10-27 17:27:20','',131,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/131-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(327,1,'2017-10-30 15:58:32','2017-10-30 15:58:32','Welcome to Aya. We believe that living plant-strong is similar to a future dominated by clean, renewable energy. We invite you to #jointheAYAlution and help us in our mission to reduce animal agriculture.\r\n\r\nWe\'re more than just plant-based we are creating a conscious business¬†that cares about its employees, the environment, our community and our shareholders. We prioritise sustainability and ethics and our purpose is to reduce animal agriculture by providing delicious plant based products.\r\n\r\nAya is an African goddess of forests, animals and herbal healing. Inspired by her, our organic plantbutter is kinder to the animals, the earth and ourselves (Aya Original contains 10% less fat than cow\'s butter and 9% less saturated fat).','About Aya','','inherit','closed','closed','','297-revision-v1','','','2017-10-30 15:58:32','2017-10-30 15:58:32','',297,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/297-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(328,1,'2017-10-30 15:59:58','2017-10-30 15:59:58','<p class=\"western\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Aya Original was created in my kitchen because, having taken up a vegan life-style, I didn\'t want to miss out on the enjoyment of butter. I created Aya Original as the closest plant alternative to cow\'s butter. Aya Original is made with coconut oil, cacao butter and safflower oil. The coconut oil and cacao butter have been steamed to remove their flavours. Cacao butter is what makes Aya so melty, it also helps it stay hard at room temperature. The safflower oil is cold pressed which is a great way of maintaining its nutritional benefits. Just like cow\'s butter Aya Original is high in fat. Aya Original has 10% lower overall fat than cow\'s butter and 9% less saturated fat. Enjoy Aya Original responsibly!</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"western\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Aya Original is great for toast and can be used for spreading, cooking and baking. Unlike a lot of other spreads on the market Aya contains no palm oil. It is organic, contains no GMO ingredients, </span></span></span><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;\"><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">and is made with 6 simple ingredients. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h4 class=\"western\">Dietary and lifestyle</h4>\r\n<p class=\"western\">ONLY ORGANIC INGREDIENTS</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">No PALM OIL</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">No GMO INGREDIENTS</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">No DAIRY OR LACTOSE</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Suitable for VEGANS and VEGETARIANS</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 class=\"western\">Ingredients</h4>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Organic steamed coconut oil (29%), organic steamed cocoa butter (22%), organic cold-pressed safflower oil (20%), spring water, Himalayan pink salt (1.4%), organic sunflower lecithin (vegetable fat 71%)</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 class=\"western\">Typical nutritional values per 100g</h4>\r\n<table border=\"1\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"4\"><colgroup><col width=\"64*\" /> <col width=\"64*\" /> <col width=\"64*\" /> <col width=\"64*\" /> </colgroup>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">Typical values</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">Per 100g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">Per 10g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">RI% based on 10g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">Energy (kJ / kCal)</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">2636 / 636</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">263 / 63</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">3%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">Total fat</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Saturated</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">71g</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">42g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">7.1g</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">4.2g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">10%</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">21%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">Carbohydrates</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">0g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">0g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">0</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">Sugar</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">0g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">0g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">0</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">Fibre</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">0g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">0g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">0</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">Protein</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">0g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">0g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">0</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">Salt</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">1.34g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">0.134g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p class=\"western\">2.24%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h4 class=\"western\">How is Aya Original made?</h4>\r\n<p class=\"western\">The oils are melted to liquid form and blended with spring water, oil and a small amount of sunflower lecithin and then put in the fridge to set.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 class=\"western\">Where are Aya Original\'s ingredients from?</h4>\r\n<p class=\"western\">We source our organic steamed cocoa butter from RealFoodSource who import the cacao from Dominican Republic. Our organic steamed coconut oil is purchased from Biona whose coconut oils originate from SriLanka and the Philippines. Our organic cold-pressed safflower oil is purchased from Kerfoot Group and originates from TO DO:</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 class=\"western\">What are the health risks associated with Aya Original?</h4>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Just like cow\'s butter Aya Original contains a high overall fat content which is composed mostly of saturated fats. Whilst Aya Original contains 10% less overall fat and 9% less saturated fat then cow\'s butter it should be consumed responsibly. Eating high levels of saturated fat can raise your cholesterol and increase your risk of heart disease.</p>\r\n<p class=\"western\">Aya Original contains 0.7% sunflower lecithin which makes 