ed with spring water, salt and a small amount of sunflower lecithin. They are poured into moulds and set in the fridge. <img title=\"Moulds\" src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/IMG_1699-opt.png\" /></p>\n\n<h3>Where are Aya Original\'s ingredients from?</h3>\n<p>We source our organic steamed cocoa butter from <a href=\"https://www.realfoodsource.com/\">RealFoodSource</a> who import the <b>cocoa from Dominican Republic</b>. Our organic steamed coconut oil is from <a href=\"http://www.kerfootgroup.co.uk/\">Kerfoot</a> whose <b>coconut oils originate from TO DO: TBC</b>. Our organic cold-pressed safflower oil is from <a href=\"http://www.meridianfoods.co.uk/\">Meridian</a> whose <b>safflower oil originates from India</b>. We use organic sunflower lecithin to give Aya a creamy and spreadable texture.  Our sunflower lecithin is sourced from <a href=\"https://www.theingredients.co.uk/\">The Ingredients Consultancy</a> whose source <b>sunflower lecithin from TO DO: TBC</b></p>\n\n<h3>What are the health risks associated with Aya Original?</h3>\n<p>Aya Original contains <b>10% less overall fat and 9% less saturated fat then cow\'s butter</b>. Aya Original has a <b>total fat content of 71%, of which 42% is saturated fat</b>. Coconut oil and cocoa butter are the main contributors to the saturated fat content. <b>Safflower oil is a healthy fat composed of predominantly poly-unsaturated fat</b>. <span class=\"emphasis\">Aya Original should be consumed responsibly as eating high levels of saturated fat can raise your cholesterol and increase risk of heart disease.</span></p>\n\n<p>Aya Original contains <b>1.5% sunflower lecithin which makes it creamy and spreadable</b>. Our organic sunflower lecithin contains &lt;1g of trans-fat per 100g thus a <span class=\"emphasis\">200g block of Aya contains &lt;0.03g of trans fat</span>.</p>','Products','','inherit','closed','closed','','343-autosave-v1','','','2018-09-14 13:19:33','2018-09-14 13:19:33','',343,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/343-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(357,1,'2017-11-13 15:48:19','2017-11-13 15:48:19','<h2>Aya Original</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Aya Original was created in my kitchen because, having taken up a vegan life-style, I didn\'t want to miss out on the enjoyment of butter. I created Aya Original as the closest plant alternative to cow\'s butter. Aya Original is made with coconut oil, cacao butter and safflower oil. The coconut oil and cacao butter have been steamed to remove their flavours. Cacao butter is what makes Aya so melty, it also helps it stay hard at room temperature. The safflower oil is cold pressed which is a great way of maintaining its nutritional benefits. Just like cow\'s butter Aya Original is high in fat. Aya Original has 10% lower overall fat than cow\'s butter and 9% less saturated fat. Enjoy Aya Original responsibly!</p>\r\n<p>Aya Original is great for toast and can be used for spreading, cooking and baking. Unlike a lot of other spreads on the market Aya contains no palm oil. It is organic, contains no GMO ingredients and is made with 6 simple ingredients.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Dietary and lifestyle</h3>\r\n<p>ONLY ORGANIC INGREDIENTS</p>\r\n<p>No PALM OIL</p>\r\n<p>No GMO INGREDIENTS</p>\r\n<p>No DAIRY OR LACTOSE</p>\r\n<p>Suitable for VEGANS and VEGETARIANS</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Ingredients</h3>\r\n<p>Organic steamed coconut oil, organic steamed cocoa butter, organic cold-pressed safflower oil , spring water, Himalayan pink salt , organic sunflower lecithin (vegetable fat 71%)</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Typical nutritional values per 100g</h3>\r\n<table>\r\n<colgroup><col width=\"64*\" /> <col width=\"64*\" /> <col width=\"64*\" /> <col width=\"64*\" /> </colgroup>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p>Typical values</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p>Per 100g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p>Per 10g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"25%\">\r\n<p>RI% based on 10g</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td wi