ical and analytical.  We wanted to to expose the weeds and acknowledge the areas of weakness.  We made comparisons about the validity of our idea compared with those that were successful, keen to discover the key to their success.</p>\r\n<p>When I think about success and failure they are two sides to the same coin.  In both scenarios we have a vision, set a goal, make a plan and execute it.  It is only the final outcome that is different.  I believe that the best thing we can do to alleviate the suffering we create around failure is to respond to failure as we do in success.  We can glow with pride and smile with accomplishment because we gave it a go, because without those that try, those that are willing to expose themselves and make themselves vulnerable humanity will not progress.  If we can fail in the knowledge that we will learn from our mistakes, then we can create a new culture where individuals are inspired to try without fear and the stigma of failure.  If in failure we can be equally retrospective and analytical about our strengths and our weaknesses then we can play a better, stronger hand and we can celebrate our strengths despite failure. And just as importantly, if in success we can maintain humility, if we reject feelings of superiority, grandiosity and importance and if we respond just as we do in failure then we narrow the gap between success and failure and we highlight the significance and importance of the journey rather than the achievement of a goal.</p>\r\n<div>\r\n     <section class=\"\">\r\n        <div class=\"\">\r\n            <ul class=\"list-inline text-center\">\r\n                <li>\r\n                    <a class=\"\" href=\"https://twitter.com/ayaplantbased\">\r\n                        <span class=\"fa-stack fa-lg\">\r\n                            <i class=\"fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x\"></i>\r\n                            <i class=\"fa fa-twitter fa-stack-1x fa-inverse\"></i>\r\n                        </span>\r\n               