ruggle, we can be who we want to be.\r\n\r\nBrowse the <a class=\"emphasis\" href=\"/recipe/list/all\"><strong>recipes</strong></a> to be inspired by simple meat-free and dairy-free meals and treats. Read our <a href=\"/article/list/all\"><strong>articles</strong></a>¬†to get¬†updates on what we are working on and how we have been motivated. Enjoy our <a href=\"/inspiration/list/all\"><strong>inspiration</strong></a> pictures and quotes to¬†awaken your heart. And if you <a href=\"/register\"><strong>register</strong></a> then you too can¬†add to our collection of recipes and inspirations!','Call of the Forest','','inherit','closed','closed','','28-revision-v1','','','2018-09-01 10:11:26','2018-09-01 10:11:26','',28,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/28-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(528,1,'2018-09-01 10:21:29','2018-09-01 10:21:29','<p>We value your feedback! We can only grow and develop with you in mind.  Please share your opinions, inspiration, photos, questions, recipes, whatever you have in mind, we can\'t wait to hear from you!</p>','Contact','','inherit','closed','closed','','329-revision-v1','','','2018-09-01 10:21:29','2018-09-01 10:21:29','',329,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/329-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(529,1,'2018-09-01 10:21:37','2018-09-01 10:21:37','<h2>Aya Original</h2>\r\n<p>Aya Original our closest organic plantbased alternative to dairy butter.  It\'s <strong>creamy</strong>, <strong>melty</strong> and has a <strong>delicious delicate</strong> flavour.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We encourage you to try Aya on warm toast (so melty and scrummy) and bread (creamy and soft), for cooking (think mushrooms sizzling in plantbutter) or for baking (substitute Aya for butter).</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Dietary and lifestyle</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"ayaList\">\r\n 	<li>ONLY ORGANIC INGREDIENTS</li>\r\n 	<li>No PALM OIL</li>\r\n 	<li>No GMO INGREDIENTS</li>\r\n 	<li>No DAIRY OR LACTOSE</li>\r\n 	<li>Suitable for VEGANS and VEGETARIANS</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Ingredients</h3>\r\n<p>The plant oils in Aya Original are coconut oil, cacao butter and safflower oil. The coconut oil and cacao butter have been steamed to remove their flavours. Cacao butter is what makes Aya so melty, it also helps it stay hard at room temperature. The safflower oil is cold pressed which is a great way of maintaining its nutritional benefits.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Organic steamed coconut oil, organic steamed cocoa butter, organic cold-pressed safflower oil , spring water, Himalayan pink salt , organic sunflower lecithin</strong> (vegetable fat spread 71%)</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Typical nutritional values per 100g</h3>\r\n<table class=\"table table-striped\"><colgroup> <col /> <col /></colgroup>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Typical values</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Per 100g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Energy (kJ/kCal)</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">2636 / 636</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Total fat</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">71g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Saturated</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">42g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Carbohydrates</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Sugar</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Fibre</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Protein</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Salt</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">1.34g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h3>How is Aya Original made?</h3>\r\n<p>The oils are melted to liquid form. Whilst cooling the oils are blended with spring water, salt and a small amount of sunflower lecithin. They are poured into moulds and set in the fridge. <img title=\"Moulds\" src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/IMG_1699-opt.png\" /></p>\r\n<h3>Where are Aya Original\'s ingredients from?</h3>\r\n<p>We source our organic steamed cocoa butter from <a href=\"https://www.realfoodsource.com/\">RealFoodSource</a> who import the cacao from Dominican Republic. Our organic steamed coconut oil is from <a href=\"http://biona.co.uk/\">Biona</a> whose coconut oils originate from SriLanka and the Philippines. Our organic cold-pressed safflower oil is from <a href=\"http://www.meridianfoods.co.uk/\">Meridian</a> and originates from India.</p>\r\n<h3>What are the health risks associated with Aya Original?</h3>\r\n<p>Aya Original contains 10% less overall fat and 9% less saturated fat then cow\'s butter. Aya Original has a total fat content of 71%, of which 42% is saturated fat. Coconut oil and cocoa butter are the main contributors to the saturated fat content. Safflower oil is a healthy fat composed of predominantly poly-unsaturated fat. Aya Original should be consumed responsibly as eating high levels of saturated fat can raise your cholesterol and increase your risk of heart disease.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aya Original contains 0.7% sunflower lecithin which makes it creamy and spreadable. Sunflower lecithin contains &lt;1g of trans-fat per 100g.</p>','Products','','inherit','closed','closed','','343-revision-v1','','','2018-09-01 10:21:37','2018-09-01 10:21:37','',343,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/343-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(530,1,'2018-09-01 10:21:45','2018-09-01 10:21:45','<p>We believe that our business should hold your values in our highest regard so that you can rest assured that your money is being used for the highest good.<p>\r\n\r\n<p>As a conscious business we are prioritising transparency and social responsibility:</p>\r\n<ul class=\"ayaList\">\r\n<li>Aya believes that a diet rich in plant-strong foods is a better way for us to take care of ourselves and the planet.  We support plantbased choices and healthy living is our highest priority. </li>\r\n<li>We are committed to sourcing high quality, organic ingredients that minimise processing techniques.  We will never use genetically modified organic (GMO) ingredients and we will never use processing techniques that use toxins. We will always support sustainable and ethically sourced ingredients and will always favour those with accreditations that validate these.</li>\r\n<li>We will always provide you with information about what our products contain, how they are made and where the ingredients are sourced.</li>\r\n<li>We will consistently access our overall impact on the environment through ongoing environmental impact assessments (EIA).</li>\r\n<li>We are committed to ethical trade and adhere to the Ethical Trade Initiative Basic Code, United Nations Declaration of Human Rights and the International Labour Organisation Core Conventions.</li>\r\n<li>We will always provide a fair livelihood for all our employees.  We believe that an individual\'s work should offer in return a sustainable and fair livelihood as well as job satisfaction.  We understand that the role of work is only one aspect of an individual\'s life and that happiness can only be achieved in a holistic and balanced way of living.</li> \r\n<li>We committed to minimising its impact on the environment by:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Ensuring our activities are efficient, effective and comply with legal requirements and environmental policies.</li> \r\n<li>Using environmentally friendly transport wherever possible.</li> \r\n<li>Maximising the use of alternative green or sustainable energy (solar and wind energy) and resources (reused and recycled).</li>\r\n<li>Reducing and minimising the use of hazardous materials and ensuring that the handling and disposal of hazardous materials is safe and reliable.</li>\r\n<li>Minimising packaging and choosing biodegradable, compostable and recycled alternatives wherever possible.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>','Our story','','inherit','closed','closed','','297-revision-v1','','','2018-09-01 10:21:45','2018-09-01 10:21:45','',297,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/2