ssed and put into words when it is one-sided. Everything that can be thought with the mind and said with words is one-sided, it\'s all just the half of it, lacking completeness, roundness, or unity.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p>Siddhartha by Hermann Hesse</p>','Conscious eating','','inherit','closed','closed','','131-revision-v1','','','2018-09-07 12:02:18','2018-09-07 12:02:18','',131,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/131-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(602,1,'2018-09-13 15:22:08','2018-09-13 15:22:08','<img src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/aya-product-1.png\" alt=\"aya-product-1\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-566\" />\r\n<h2>Simple, honest, clean plantbutters</h2>\r\nOur plantbutters are simple, honest and clean, here\'s how:\r\n<h3>SIMPLE</h3>\r\nOur plantbutters were dreamed up in Amy\'s home kitchen using domestic equipment and organic ingredients. Amy\'s motivation was to create a <b>delicious tasting, plantbased alternative to dairy butter</b> because plantbutter <a href=\"http://www.conservationmagazine.org/2014/03/butter-vs-margarine-environmental/\"><b>has a four times lower carbon footprint than dairy butter</b></a> and has no association with animal cruelty often linked to the conventional dairy industry.\r\n<h3>HONEST</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"aya-emphasis-list\">\r\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">SINCERE</span> - We will <b>always provide you with information</b> about what our products contain, how they are made and where the ingredients are sourced.</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">SUSTAINABLE</span> - We are a sustainable business that ensures that all activities related to our business <b>consider the impact it has on the environment</b> and the ability of future generations to meet their own needs.\r\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">CONSCIOUS BUSINESS</span> - We believe that our business should align with your highest values so that <b>when you choose our products you are doing the greatest good for the earth and all its beings</b>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>CLEAN</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"aya-emphasis-list\">\r\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">NO HEXANE</span> - We use only organic ingredients which means our ingredients are <b>grown with natural, organic fertilisers and pesticides and do not undergo any toxic processing</b>. Our plant oils have been extracted without solvents unlike un-organic oils which use Hexane, a petroleum derivative, to extract non-organic oils from their seeds.</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">NO PALM-OIL</span> - We <b>prefer cocoa butter</b> which is naturally firm at room temperature and which gives our plantbutters their unique melt-in-the-mouth quality just like dairy butter.</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">NO GMO</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">NO DAIRY</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">NO GLUTEN</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">NO PLASTIC</span> - We package our plantbutters in <b>compostable packaging</b> and we will never use plastic.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Who is Aya</h2>\r\n<b>Aya is a west African Goddess of forests, she protects the forest and its animals and she teaches her tribe how to use the plants to sustain and heal themselves. We chose the name Aya because we align with her values.</b>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/aya-forest.jpg\" alt=\"aya-forest\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-562\" />\r\n','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','287-revision-v1','','','2018-09-13 15:22:08','2018-09-13 15:22:08','',287,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/287-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(605,1,'2018-09-14 12:47:45','2018-09-14 12:47:45','<p>We value your feedback and we can only grow and develop with you in mind.  Please share your opinions, inspiration, photos, questions, recipes, whatever you have in mind, we can\'t wait to hear from you!</p>','Contact','','inherit','closed','closed','','329-revision-v1','','','2018-09-14 12:47:45','2018-09-14 12:47:45','',329,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/329-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(607,1,'2018-09-17 15:00:29','2018-09-17 15:00:29','<p class=\"text-center\">\r\n<img src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/aya-original-1.png\" alt=\"aya-original\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-733\" />\r\n</p>\r\n<h2>Aya Original</h2>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\">Aya Original is our first offering.  We chose Aya Original as our first product because it is the closest <b>organic plantbased alternative to dairy butter</b>.  It\'s <span class=\"emphasis\">creamy</span>, <span class=\"emphasis\">melty</span> and has a <span class=\"emphasis\">delicious, delicate</span> flavour.  We would like everyone to choose Aya Original over dairy butter because plantbutter <a href=\"http://www.conservationmagazine.org/2014/03/butter-vs-margarine-environmental/\"><b>has a four times lower carbon footprint than dairy butter</b></a> and has no association with animal cruelty often linked to the conventional dairy industry.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"blue text-justify\">We encourage you to try Aya on warm toast (so melty and scrummy) and bread (creamy and soft), for cooking (think mushrooms sizzling in plantbutter) or for baking (substitute Aya for butter).</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Ingredients</h3>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\"><span class=\"emphasis\">Organic steamed coconut oil, water, organic steamed cocoa butter, organic cold-pressed safflower oil, Himalayan pink salt , organic sunflower lecithin</span> <b>(vegetable fat spread 71%)</b></p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\">The coconut oil and cacao butter have been steamed to remove their flavours. Cocoa butter is what gives Aya its melt-in-the-mouth quality, it also helps it stay hard at room temperature. Our safflower oil is <b>cold pressed</b> which is a great way of maintaining its nutritional benefits.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Dietary and lifestyle</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"ayaList\">\r\n 	<li>ORGANIC INGREDIENTS</li>\r\n<li>NO GMO INGREDIENTS</li>\r\n 	<li>NO PALM OIL</li>\r\n 	<li>NO DAIRY OR LACTOSE</li>\r\n<li>No GLUTEN</li>\r\n 	<li>Suitable for VEGANS</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Typical nutritional values per 100g</h3>\r\n<table class=\"table table-striped\"><colgroup> <col /> <col /></colgroup>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Typical values</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Per 100g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Energy (kJ/kCal)</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">2636 / 636</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Total fat</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">71g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Saturated</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">42g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Carbohydrates</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Sugar</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Fibre</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Protein</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Salt</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">1.34g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3>Where are Aya Original\'s ingredients from?</h3>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\">We source our organic steamed cocoa butter from <a href=\"https://www.realfoodsource.com/\">RealFoodSource</a> who import the <b>cocoa from Dominican Republic</b>. Our organic steamed coconut oil is from <a href=\"http://www.kerfootgroup.co.uk/\">Kerfoot</a> whose <b>coconut oils originate from Philipines and / or India</b>. Our organic cold-pressed safflower oil is from <a href=\"http://www.meridianfoods.co.uk/\">Meridian</a> whose <b>safflower oil originates from India</b>. We use organic sunflower lecithin to give Aya a creamy and spreadable texture.  Our sunflower lecithin is sourced from <a href=\"https://www.theingredients.co.uk/\">The Ingredients Consultancy</a> whose source <b>sunflower lecithin from a variety of countries (Bulgaria, China, Croatia, France, Germany, India, Italy, Kazakhstan, Netherlands, Austria, Poland, Romania, Russia, Serbia, Slovakia, Slovenia, Spain, Czech Republic, Turkey, Ukraine, Hungary and USA).</b></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What are the health risks associated with Aya Original?</h3>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\">Aya Original contains <b>10% less overall fat and 9% less saturated fat then cow\'s butter</b>. Aya Original has a <b>total fat content of 71%, of which 42% is saturated fat</b>. Coconut oil and cocoa butter are the main contributors to the saturated fat content. <b>Safflower oil is a healthy fat composed of predominantly poly-unsaturated fat</b>. <span class=\"emphasis\">Aya Original should be consumed responsibly as eating high levels of saturated fat can raise your cholesterol and increase risk of heart disease.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\">Aya Original contains <b>1.5% sunflower lecithin which makes it creamy and spreadable</b>. Our organic sunflower lecithin contains &lt;1g of trans-fat per 100g thus a <span class=\"emphasis\">200g block of Aya contains &lt;0.03g of trans fat</span>.</p>','Aya Original','','publish','open','open','','aya-original','','','2018-10-07 08:44:35','2018-10-07 08:44:35','',0,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/?p=607',0,'post','',0),(608,1,'2018-09-14 13:16:29','2018-09-14 13:16:29','<img src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/aya-product-2.png\" alt=\"aya-product-2\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-567\" />\r\n<h2>Aya Original</h2>\r\n<p>Aya Original is our first offering.  We chose Aya Original as our first product because it is the closest <b>organic plantbased alternative to dairy butter</b>.  It\'s <span class=\"emphasis\">creamy</span>, <span class=\"emphasis\">melty</span> and has a <span class=\"emphasis\">delicious, delicate</span> flavour.  We would like everyone to choose Aya Original over dairy butter because plantbutter <a href=\"http://www.conservationmagazine.org/2014/03/butter-vs-margarine-environmental/\"><b>has a four times lower carbon footprint than dairy butter</b></a> and has no association with animal cruelty often linked to the conventional dairy industry.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"blue\">We encourage you to try Aya on warm toast (so melty and scrummy) and bread (creamy and soft), for cooking (think mushrooms sizzling in plantbutter) or for baking (substitute Aya for butter).</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Ingredients</h3>\r\n<p><span class=\"emphasis\">Organic steamed coconut oil, water, organic steamed cocoa butter, organic cold-pressed safflower oil, Himalayan pink salt , organic sunflower lecithin</span> <b>(vegetable fat spread 71%)</b></p>\r\n<p>The coconut oil and cacao butter have been steamed to remove their flavours. Cocoa butter is what gives Aya its melt-in-the-mouth quality, it also helps it stay hard at room temperature. Our safflower oil is <b>cold pressed</b> which is a great way of maintaining its nutritional benefits.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Dietary and lifestyle</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"ayaList\">\r\n 	<li>ORGANIC INGREDIENTS</li>\r\n<li>NO GMO INGREDIENTS</li>\r\n 	<li>NO PALM OIL</li>\r\n 	<li>NO DAIRY OR LACTOSE</li>\r\n<li>No GLUTEN</li>\r\n 	<li>Suitable for VEGANS</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Typical nutritional values per 100g</h3>\r\n<table class=\"table table-striped\"><colgroup> <col /> <col /></colgroup>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Typical values</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Per 100g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Energy (kJ/kCal)</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">2636 / 636</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Total fat</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">71g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Saturated</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">42g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Carbohydrates</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Sugar</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Fibre</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Protein</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Salt</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">1.34g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h3>How is Aya Original made?</h3>\r\n<p>The oils are melted to liquid form. Whilst cooling the oils are blended with spring water, salt and a small amount of sunflower lecithin. They are poured into moulds and set in the fridge. <img title=\"Moulds\" src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/IMG_1699-opt.png\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Where are Aya Original\'s ingredients from?</h3>\r\n<p>We source our organic steamed cocoa butter from <a href=\"https://www.realfoodsource.com/\">RealFoodSource</a> who import the <b>cocoa from Dominican Republic</b>. Our organic steamed coconut oil is from <a href=\"http://www.kerfootgroup.co.uk/\">Kerfoot</a> whose <b>coconut oils originate from TO DO: TBC</b>. Our organic cold-pressed safflower oil is from <a href=\"http://www.meridianfoods.co.uk/\">Meridian</a> whose <b>safflower oil originates from India</b>. We use organic sunflower lecithin to give Aya a creamy and spreadable texture.  Our sunflower lecithin is sourced from <a href=\"https://www.theingredients.co.uk/\">The Ingredients Consultancy</a> whose source <b>sunflower lecithin from TO DO: TBC</b></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What are the health risks associated with Aya Original?</h3>\r\n<p>Aya Original contains <b>10% less overall fat and 9% less saturated fat then cow\'s butter</b>. Aya Original has a <b>total fat content of 71%, of which 42% is saturated fat</b>. Coconut oil and cocoa butter are the main contributors to the saturated fat content. <b>Safflower oil is a healthy fat composed of predominantly poly-unsaturated fat</b>. <span class=\"emphasis\">Aya Original should be consumed responsibly as eating high levels of saturated fat can raise your cholesterol and increase risk of heart disease.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aya Original contains <b>1.5% sunflower lecithin which makes it creamy and spreadable</b>. Our organic sunflower lecithin contains &lt;1g of trans-fat per 100g thus a <span class=\"emphasis\">200g block of Aya contains &lt;0.03g of trans fat</span>.</p>','','','inherit','closed','closed','','607-revision-v1','','','2018-09-14 13:16:29','2018-09-14 13:16:29','',607,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/607-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(609,1,'2018-09-14 13:17:13','2018-09-14 13:17:13','<img src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/aya-product-2.png\" alt=\"aya-product-2\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-567\" />\r\n<h2>Aya Original</h2>\r\n<p>Aya Original is our first offering.  We chose Aya Original as our first product because it is the closest <b>organic plantbased alternative to dairy butter</b>.  It\'s <span class=\"emphasis\">creamy</span>, <span class=\"emphasis\">melty</span> and has a <span class=\"emphasis\">delicious, delicate</span> flavour.  We would like everyone to choose Aya Original over dairy butter because plantbutter <a href=\"http://www.conservationmagazine.org/2014/03/butter-vs-margarine-environmental/\"><b>has a four times lower carbon footprint than dairy butter</b></a> and has no association with animal cruelty often linked to the conventional dairy industry.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"blue\">We encourage you to try Aya on warm toast (so melty and scrummy) and bread (creamy and soft), for cooking (think mushrooms sizzling in plantbutter) or for baking (substitute Aya for butter).</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Ingredients</h3>\r\n<p><span class=\"emphasis\">Organic steamed coconut oil, water, organic steamed cocoa butter, organic cold-pressed safflower oil, Himalayan pink salt , organic sunflower lecithin</span> <b>(vegetable fat spread 71%)</b></p>\r\n<p>The coconut oil and cacao butter have been steamed to remove their flavours. Cocoa butter is what gives Aya its melt-in-the