>We choose <span class=\"emphasis\">no palm-oil</span> because of the <a href=\"https://youtu.be/TQQXstNh45g\">catastrophic effects that palm-oil cultivation has had on our rain forests and their inhabitants</a></li>\r\n<li>We will never use plastic, we choose to <span class=\"emphasis\">package our plantbutters in compostable greaseproof paper</span> because this has the lowest environmental impact</li>\r\n<li>We prioritise sustainability above all else which means that we will always consider the impact of our activities on the the environment.  Unfortunately, we will not always be able to implement the most sustainable option if in doing so we would price ourselves out of the market; we have to exist to make a difference.  Inevitably there are trade-off\'s that we will have to make but we will always be transparent about compromises and as we grow, as we make more of an impact we will reassess our choices in a timely manner.</li>\r\n','Our story','','inherit','closed','closed','','297-revision-v1','','','2018-09-18 16:41:50','2018-09-18 16:41:50','',297,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/297-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(653,1,'2018-09-18 17:01:45','2018-09-18 17:01:45','<h2>A kinder option</h2>\r\nThe popularity of <span class=\"emphasis\">plantbased</span> foods cannot be denied and the reasons are simple; plantbased foods offer healthier options, have a far lighter tread on the environment and ensure no animal cruelty.  I started Aya because I wanted to offer you the option to choose a purely plantbased alternative to cow\'s butter and other vegetable based oil spreads which is just as tasty and just as versatile - now you can choose a kinder option whenever you like.\r\n\r\n<h2>Our values and ethics</h2>\r\nAya is far more than plantbased; our values and ethics extend to everything we do.  As a start:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>We prioritise sustainability above all else which means that we will always consider the impact of our activities on the the environment:</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>We will be a <a href=\"https://bcorporation.net/\">Certified B Corporation</a>.  Certified B Corporations meet the highest standards of verified social and environmental performance, transparency and accountability.  We are people using business as a force of good.</li>\r\n<li>We will be both <a href=\"https://www.soilassociation.org/\">Soil Association Organic</a> and <a href=\"https://www.vegansociety.com/\">The Vegan Society</a> accredited.</li>\r\n<li>We will use <a href=\"https://www.fairtrade.org.uk/\">Fairtrade Foundation</a> ingredients whenever we can.  Fairtrade is about better prices, decent working conditions, local sustainability, and fair terms of trade for farmers and workers in the developing world. It requires companies to pay sustainable prices (which must never fall lower than the market price).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li>We prioritise transparency above all else, we believe that you have a right to now what you are buying and how our business operates:</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>We will always provide you with information about what our products contain, how they are made and where the ingredients are sourced.</li>\r\n<li>We will always warn you of any healthy risks associated with our products.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>The implementation of our values now</h2>\r\nAs a business we must exist (profitably) to make a difference (offering plantbased alternatives to cow\'s butter and other vegetable based oil spreads), whilst sustainability is our highest priority, existence is our top priority.  Sometimes we will need to compromise and we will always be transparent about our compromises.  We will also re-evaluate these choices in a consistent timely manner.  The more that you (our beloved customers) support us the more we can grow and make an impact, this will enable us to implement our values without compromise.  Below are the things we are able to implement right now:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>We only use <span class=\"emphasis\">non-GMO, organic ingredients</span> because we believe that food should be natural and we do not advocate any chemicals used in the growing, cultivation or processing of our ingredients</li>\r\n<li>We choose <span class=\"emphasis\">no palm-oil</span> because of the <a href=\"https://youtu.be/TQQXstNh45g\">catastrophic effects that palm-oil cultivation has had on our rain forests and their inhabitants</a></li>\r\n<li>We will never use plastic, we choose to <span class=\"emphasis\">package our plantbutters in compostable greaseproof paper</span> because this has the lowest environmental impact</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','Our story','','inherit','closed','closed','','297-revision-v1','','','2018-09-18 17:01:45','2018-09-18 17:01:45','',297,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/297-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(654,1,'2018-09-19 10:46:04','2018-09-19 10:46:04','<h2>A kinder option</h2>\r\nThe popularity of <span class=\"emphasis\">plantbased</span> foods cannot be denied and the reasons are simple; plantbased foods offer healthier options, have a far lighter tread on the environment and ensure no animal cruelty.  I started Aya because I wanted to offer you the option to choose a purely plantbased alternative to cow\'s butter and other vegetable based oil spreads which is just as tasty and just as versatile - now you can choose a kinder option whenever you like.\r\n\r\n<h2>Our values and ethics</h2>\r\nAya is far more than plantbased; our values and ethics extend to everything we do.  As a start:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>We prioritise <span class=\"emphasis\">sustainability</span> which means that we will always consider the impact of our activities on the the environment:</li>\r\n<li>We prioritise <span class=\"emphasis\">transparency</span> which means we believe that you have a right to know exactly what you are buying and how our business operates:</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>We will always provide you with information about what our products contain, how they are made and where the ingredients are sourced.</li>\r\n<li