layan pink salt , organic sunflower lecithin</span> <b>(vegetable fat spread 71%)</b></p>\r\n<p>The coconut oil and cacao butter have been steamed to remove their flavours. Cocoa butter is what gives Aya its melt-in-the-mouth quality, it also helps it stay hard at room temperature. Our safflower oil is <b>cold pressed</b> which is a great way of maintaining its nutritional benefits.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Dietary and lifestyle</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"ayaList\">\r\n 	<li>ORGANIC INGREDIENTS</li>\r\n<li>NO GMO INGREDIENTS</li>\r\n 	<li>NO PALM OIL</li>\r\n 	<li>NO DAIRY OR LACTOSE</li>\r\n<li>No GLUTEN</li>\r\n 	<li>Suitable for VEGANS</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Typical nutritional values per 100g</h3>\r\n<table class=\"table table-striped\"><colgroup> <col /> <col /></colgroup>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Typical values</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Per 100g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Energy (kJ/kCal)</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">2636 / 636</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Total fat</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">71g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Saturated</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">42g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Carbohydrates</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Sugar</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Fibre</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Protein</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Salt</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">1.34g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3>Where are Aya Original\'s ingredients from?</h3>\r\n<p>We source our organic steamed cocoa butter from <a href=\"https://www.realfoodsource.com/\">RealFoodSource</a> who import the <b>cocoa from Dominican Republic</b>. Our organic steamed coconut oil is from <a href=\"http://www.kerfootgroup.co.uk/\">Kerfoot</a> whose <b>coconut oils originate from Philipines and / or India</b>. Our organic cold-pressed safflower oil is from <a href=\"http://www.meridianfoods.co.uk/\">Meridian</a> whose <b>safflower oil originates from India</b>. We use organic sunflower lecithin to give Aya a creamy and spreadable texture.  Our sunflower lecithin is sourced from <a href=\"https://www.theingredients.co.uk/\">The Ingredients Consultancy</a> whose source <b>sunflower lecithin from a variety of countries (Bulgaria, China, Croatia, France, Germany, India, Italy, Kazakhstan, Netherlands, Austria, Poland, Romania, Russia, Serbia, Slovakia, Slovenia, Spain, Czech Republic, Turkey, Ukraine, Hungary and USA).</b></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What are the health risks associated with Aya Original?</h3>\r\n<p>Aya Original contains <b>10% less overall fat and 9% less saturated fat then cow\'s butter</b>. Aya Original has a <b>total fat content of 71%, of which 42% is saturated fat</b>. Coconut oil and cocoa butter are the main contributors to the saturated fat content. <b>Safflower oil is a healthy fat composed of predominantly poly-unsaturated fat</b>. <span class=\"emphasis\">Aya Original should be consumed responsibly as eating high levels of saturated fat can raise your cholesterol and increase risk of heart disease.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aya Original contains <b>1.5% sunflower lecithin which makes it creamy and spreadable</b>. Our organic sunflower lecithin contains &lt;1g of trans-fat per 100g thus a <span class=\"emphasis\">200g block of Aya contains &lt;0.03g of trans fat</span>.</p>','Aya Original','','inherit','closed','closed','','607-revision-v1','','','2018-09-19 11:33:47','2018-09-19 11:33:47','',607,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/607-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(662,1,'2018-09-19 11:35:19','2018-09-19 11:35:19','<img src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/aya-original.png\" alt=\"aya-original\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-631\" />