:31:59','<h1 class=\"visible-xs-block\">Aya Spreadable</h1>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\">We\'re super excited about our next variety of Aya - Aya Spreadable.  Aya contains cold pressed linseed oil which gives it it\'s delicious flavour and which is great source of omega-3.  Unlike Aya Original we do not recommend using Aya Spreadable for cooking and baking because linseed oxidises at high temperatures.  Aya Spreadable is perfect for spreading on bread and toast, melting over veges or popcorn and even making delicious plantbased butter icing.</p>','Aya Spreadable','','inherit','closed','closed','','621-revision-v1','','','2018-09-20 15:31:59','2018-09-20 15:31:59','',621,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/621-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(723,1,'2018-09-20 15:34:52','2018-09-20 15:34:52','<h1 class=\"visible-xs-block\">Aya Spreadable</h1>\r\n<p class=\"center image-75\">\r\n<img src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/aya-original.png\" alt=\"aya-original\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-631\" />\r\n</p>\r\n<h2>Aya Original</h2>\r\n<p class=\"justify\">Aya Original is our first offering.  We chose Aya Original as our first product because it is the closest <b>organic plantbased alternative to dairy butter</b>.  It\'s <span class=\"emphasis\">creamy</span>, <span class=\"emphasis\">melty</span> and has a <span class=\"emphasis\">delicious, delicate</span> flavour.  We would like everyone to choose Aya Original over dairy butter because plantbutter <a href=\"http://www.conservationmagazine.org/2014/03/butter-vs-margarine-environmental/\"><b>has a four times lower carbon footprint than dairy butter</b></a> and has no association with animal cruelty often linked to the conventional dairy industry.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"blue justify\">We encourage you to try Aya on warm toast (so melty and scrummy) and bread (creamy and soft), for cooking (think mushrooms sizzling in plantbutter) or for baking (substitute Aya for butter).</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Ingredients</h3>\r\n<p class=\"justify\"><span class=\"emphasis\">Organic steamed coconut oil, water, organic steamed cocoa butter, organic cold-pressed safflower oil, Himalayan pink salt , organic sunflower lecithin</span> <b>(vegetable fat spread 71%)</b></p>\r\n<p class=\"justify\">The coconut oil and cacao butter have been steamed to remove their flavours. Cocoa butter is what gives Aya its melt-in-the-mouth quality, it also helps it stay hard at room temperature. Our safflower oil is <b>cold pressed</b> which is a great way of maintaining its nutritional benefits.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Dietary and lifestyle</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"ayaList\">\r\n 	<li>ORGANIC INGREDIENTS</li>\r\n<li>NO GMO INGREDIENTS</li>\r\n 	<li>NO PALM OIL</li>\r\n 	<li>NO DAIRY OR LACTOSE</li>\r\n<li>No GLUTEN</li>\r\n 	<li>Suitable for VEGANS</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Typical nutritional values per 100g</h3>\r\n<table class=\"table table-striped\"><colgroup> <col /> <col /></colgroup>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Typical values</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Per 100g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Energy (kJ/kCal)</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">2636 / 636</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Total fat</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">71g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Saturated</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">42g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Carbohydrates</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Sugar</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Fibre</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Protein</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Salt</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">1.34g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3>Where are Aya Original\'s ingredients from?</h3>\r\n<p class=\"justify\">We source our organic steamed cocoa butter from <a href=\"https://www.realfoodsource.com/\">RealFoodSource</a> who import the <b>cocoa from Dominican Republic</b>. Our organic steamed coconut oil is from <a href=\"http://www.kerfootgroup.co.uk/\">Kerfoot</a> whose <b>coconut oils originate from Philipines and / or India</b>. Our organic cold-pressed safflower oil is from <a href=\"http://www.meridianfoods.co.uk/\">Meridian</a> whose <b>safflower oil originates from India</b>. We use organic sunflower lecithin to give Aya a creamy and spreadable texture.  Our sunflower lecithin is sourced from <a href=\"https://www.theingredients.co.uk/\">The Ingredients Consultancy</a> whose source <b>sunflower lecithin from a variety of countries (Bulgaria, China, Croatia, France, Germany, India, Italy, Kazakhstan, Netherlands, Austria, Poland, Romania, Russia, Serbia, Slovakia, Slovenia, Spain, Czech Republic, Turkey, Ukraine, Hungary and USA).</b></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What are the health risks associated with Aya Original?</h3>\r\n<p class=\"justify\">Aya Original contains <b>10% less overall fat and 9% less saturated fat then cow\'s butter</b>. Aya Original has a <b>total fat content of 71%, of which 42% is saturated fat</b>. Coconut oil and cocoa butter are the main contributors to the saturated fat content. <b>Safflower oil is a healthy fat composed of predominantly poly-unsaturated fat</b>. <span class=\"emphasis\">Aya Original should be consumed responsibly as eating high levels of saturated fat can raise your cholesterol and increase risk of heart disease.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"justify\">Aya Original contains <b>1.5% sunflower lecithin which makes it creamy and spreadable</b>. Our organic sunflower lecithin contains &lt;1g of trans-fat per 100g thus a <span class=\"emphasis\">200g block of Aya contains &lt;0.03g of trans fat</span>.</p>','Aya Original','','inherit','closed','closed','','607-revision-v1','','','2018-09-20 15:34:52','2018-09-20 15:34:52','',607,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/607-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(724,1,'2018-09-20 15:58:38','2018-09-20 15:58:38','<h1 class=\"visible-xs-block\">Our Story</h1>\r\n<div class=\"col-lg-10\">\r\n<p class=\"text-center\">\r\n<img src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/aya-product-3.png\" alt=\"aya-product-3\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-692\" />\r\n</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2>A kinder option</h2>\r\n<p class=\"justify\">The popularity of <span class=\"emphasis\">plantbased</span> foods cannot be denied and the reasons are simple; plantbased foods offer healthier options, have a far lighter tread on the environment and ensure no animal cruelty.  I started Aya because I wanted to offer you the option to choose a purely plantbased alternative to cow\'s butter and other vegetable based oil spreads which is just as tasty and just as versatile - now you can choose a kinder option whenever you like.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote class=\"inline-quote\">\r\n<p class=\"blockquote\">The more we grow and make an impact the more we will be able to make demands that align with our highest values but we will need your loyalty to get there.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<h2>Our values and ethics</h2>\r\nAya is far more than plantbased; our values and ethics extend to everything we do.  As a start:\r\n<ul class=\"ayaList\">\r\n<li>We prioritise <span class=\"emphasis\">sustainability</span> which means that we will always consider the impact of our activities on the the environment:</li>\r\n<li>We prioritise <span class=\"emphasis\">transparency</span> which means we believe that you have a right to know exactly what you are buying and how our business operates:</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>We will always provide you with information about what our products contain, how they are made and where the ingredients are sourced.</li>\r\n<li>We will always warn you of any health risks associated with our products.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li>We prioritise <span class=\"emphasis\">ethical trade</span> and adhere to the Ethical Trade Initiative Basic Code, United Nations Declaration of Human Rights and the International Labour Organisation Core Conventions.</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>We will always provide a fair livelihood for all our employees.  We believe that an individual\'s work should offer in return a sustainable and fair livelihood as well as job satisfaction.  We understand that the role of work is only one aspect of an individual\'s life and that happiness can only be achieved in a holistic and balanced way of living.\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"justify\">As a start-up we realise the importance of creating a profitable business that aligns with our core values.  We must be profitable so that we can pay our employees, provide a comfortable and conducive working environment and pay our investors a fair return on their investment.  Sometimes we may have to make a small compromise on our values but we will always do so with openness and inform you of our decision.  We will then consistently reassess our decisions in a timely manner.</p> \r\n\r\n<h3>This is what we have implemented so far:</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"ayaList\">\r\n<li>We only use <span class=\"emphasis\">non-GMO, organic ingredients</span> because we believe that food should be natural and we do not advocate any chemicals used in the growing, cultivation or processing of our ingredients</li>\r\n<li>We choose <span class=\"emphasis\">no palm-oil</span> because of the <a href=\"https://youtu.be/TQQXstNh45g\">catastrophic effects that palm-oil cultivation has had on our rain forests and their inhabitants</a></li>\r\n<li>We will never use plastic, we choose to <span class=\"emphasis\">package our plantbutters in compostable greaseproof paper</span> because this has the lowest environmental impact.  We encourage butter dishes as a way of preserving your butter in the fridge.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>And this is what we intend to implement as soon as we possibly can:</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"ayaList\">\r\n<li>We will be a <a href=\"https://bcorporation.net/\">Certified B Corporation</a>.  Certified B Corporations meet the highest standards of verified social and environmental performance, transparency and accountability. B Corporations are people using business as a force of good.</li>\r\n<li>We will be both <a href=\"https://www.soilassociation.org/\">Soil Association Organic</a> and <a href=\"https://www.vegansociety.com/\">The Vegan Society</a> accredited.</li>\r\n<li>We will use <a href=\"https://www.fairtrade.org.uk/\">Fairtrade Foundation</a> ingredients whenever we can.  Fairtrade is about better prices, decent working conditions, local sustainability and fair terms of trade for farmers and workers in the developing world. It requires companies to pay sustainable prices (which must never fall lower than the market price).</li>\r\n</ul>','Our story','','inherit','closed','closed','','297-revision-v1','','','2018-09-20 15:58:38','2018-09-20 15:58:38','',297,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/297-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(725,1,'2018-09-20 16:02:00','2018-09-20 16:02:00','<p class=\"text-right green\">14th October 2016</p>\r\n<p>I have been consuming a vegan and organic diet for the past two years. I made the decision for ethical reasons due to my concerns with the mistreatment of animals in the meat and dairy industry as well as the strain that animal agriculture and chemicals have on the environment.</p>\r\n<p>Initially this was a relaxed decision, however as the years have gone¬†by I am finding it increasingly difficult to eat meat, dairy or non-organic food.</p>\r\n<p>Eating a vegan diet¬†has an interesting learning curve.¬† One has to meet all¬†their nutritional requirements without meat or dairy sources.¬† It\'s not impossible but it does take some careful choices and a clear understanding of the nutrients we need and in what foods they are found.¬† It also requires listening to your body and noticing when things aren\'t quite right.</p>\r\n<p>I\'ve noticed that I¬†depend on¬†¬†lots of¬†\'exotic\' ingredients that aren\'t sourced locally.¬† Things like hemp seeds, chia seeds and Spirulina.¬† In fact most of my protein sources like chickpeas, kidney beans, quinoa and lentils are not sourced locally.¬† It has me wondering if I am creating a¬†bigger carbon footprint than if I just ate locally sourced ingredients which might include meat and dairy.</p>\r\n<p>The point is that if¬†it were proven that my carbon footprint¬†was larger than if I ate locally sourced foods I would reconsider my choices.¬† Which brings me back to the aversion I have eating meat, dairy or non-organic food.¬† Have I become identified with being vegan?¬† Does it give me satisfaction to say \'I\'m vegan\'?¬† Do I think I am better than others and judge them because they aren\'t vegan?¬† Being identified with veganism is of little benefit as it means that I¬†have become¬†closed to new¬†information and defensive about my¬†opinions.</p>\r\n<p>That\'s why I¬†believe that eating consciously is most important.¬† It\'s not about making judgements or identifications, its about acting for the greatest good.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote class=\"inline-quote\">\r\n<p class=\"blockquote\">In every truth the opposite is equally true.¬†That is to say, any truth can only be expressed and put into words when it is one-sided. Everything that can be thought with the mind and said with words is one-sided, it\'s all just the half of it, lacking completeness, roundness, or unity.</p><footer>Siddhartha by<cite title=\"\"> Hermann Hesse</cite></footer></blockquote>\r\n','Conscious eating','','inherit','closed','closed','','131-revision-v1','','','2018-09-20 16:02:00','2018-09-20 16:02:00','',131,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/131-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(726,1,'2018-09-20 16:02:44','2018-09-20 16:02:44','<p class=\"text-right green\">14th October 2016</p>\r\n<p>I have been consuming a vegan and organic diet for the past two years. I made the decision for ethical reasons due to my concerns with the mistreatment of animals in the meat and dairy industry as well as the strain that animal agriculture and chemicals have on the environment.</p>\r\n<p>Initially this was a relaxed decision, however as the years have gone¬†by I am finding it increasingly difficult to eat meat, dairy or non-organic food.</p>\r\n<p>Eating a vegan diet¬†has an interesting learning curve.¬† One has to meet all¬†their nutritional requirements without meat or dairy sources.¬† It\'s not impossible but it does take some careful choices and a clear understanding of the nutrients we need and in what foods they are found.¬† It also requires listening to your body and noticing when things aren\'t quite right.</p>\r\n<p>I\'ve noticed that I¬†depend on¬†¬†lots of¬†\'exotic\' ingredients that aren\'t sourced locally.¬† Things like hemp seeds, chia seeds and Spirulina.¬† In fact most of my protein sources like chickpeas, kidney beans, quinoa and lentils are not sourced locally.¬† It has me wondering if I am creating a¬†bigger carbon footprint than if I just ate locally sourced ingredients which might include meat and dairy.</p>\r\n<p>The point is that if¬†it were proven that my carbon footprint¬†was larger than if I ate locally sourced foods I would reconsider my choices.¬† Which brings me back to the aversion I have eating meat, dairy or non-organic food.¬† Have I become identified with being vegan?¬† Does it give me satisfaction to say \'I\'m vegan\'?¬† Do I think I am better than others and judge them because they aren\'t vegan?¬† Being identified with veganism is of little benefit as it means that I¬†have become¬†closed to new¬†information and defensive about my¬†opinions.</p>\r\n<p>That\'s why I¬†believe that eating consciously is most important.¬† It\'s not about making judgements or identifications, its about acting for the greatest good.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote class=\"inline-quote\">\r\n<p class=\"blockquote\">In every truth the opposite is equally true.¬†That is to say, any truth can only be expressed and put into words when it is one-sided. Everything that can be thought with the mind and said with words is one-sided, it\'s all just the half of it, lacking completeness, roundness, or unity.</p><footer>Siddhartha by Hermann Hesse</footer></blockquote>\r\n','Conscious eating','','inherit','closed','closed','','131-revision-v1','','','2018-09-20 16:02:44','2018-09-20 16:02:44','',131,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/131-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(727,1,'2018-09-20 16:05:56','2018-09-20 16:05:56','<h1 class=\"visible-xs-block\">Our Story</h1>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"text-center\">\r\n<img src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/aya-product-3.png\" alt=\"aya-product-3\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-692\" />\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>A kinder option</h2>\r\n<p class=\"justify\">The popularity of <span class=\"emphasis\">plantbased</span> foods cannot be denied and the reasons are simple; plantbased foods offer healthier options, have a far lighter tread on the environment and ensure no animal cruelty.  I started Aya because I wanted to offer you the option to choose a purely plantbased alternative to cow\'s butter and other vegetable based oil spreads which is just as tasty and just as versatile - now you can choose a kinder option whenever you like.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote class=\"inline-quote\">\r\n<p class=\"blockquote\">The more we grow and make an impact the more we will be able to make demands that align with our highest values but we will need your loyalty to get there.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<h2>Our values and ethics</h2>\r\nAya is far more than plantbased; our values and ethics extend to everything we do.  As a start:\r\n<ul class=\"ayaList\">\r\n<li>We prioritise <span class=\"emphasis\">sustainability</span> which means that we will always consider the impact of our activities on the the environment:</li>\r\n<li>We prioritise <span class=\"emphasis\">transparency</span> which means we believe that you have a right to know exactly what you are buying and how our business operates:</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>We will always provide you with information about what our products contain, how they are made and where the ingredients are sourced.</li>\r\n<li>We will always warn you of any health risks associated with our products.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li>We prioritise <span class=\"emphasis\">ethical trade</span> and adhere to the Ethical Trade Initiative Basic Code, United Nations Declaration of Human Rights and the International Labour Organisation Core Conventions.</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>We will always provide a fair livelihood for all our employees.  We believe that an individual\'s work should offer in return a sustainable and fair livelihood as well as job satisfaction.  We understand that the role of work is only one aspect of an individual\'s life and that happiness can only be achieved in a holistic and balanced way of living.\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"justify\">As a start-up we realise the importance of creating a profitable business that aligns with our core values.  We must be profitable so that we can pay our employees, provide a comfortable and conducive working environment and pay our investors a fair return on their investment.  Sometimes we may have to make a small compromise on our values but we will always do so with openness and inform you of our decision.  We will then consistently reassess our decisions in a timely manner.</p> \r\n\r\n<h3>This is what we have implemented so far:</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"ayaList\">\r\n<li>We only use <span class=\"emphasis\">non-GMO, organic ingredients</span> because we believe that food should be natural and we do not advocate any chemicals used in the growing, cultivation or processing of our ingredients</li>\r\n<li>We choose <span class=\"emphasis\">no palm-oil</span> because of the <a href=\"https://youtu.be/TQQXstNh45g\">catastrophic effects that palm-oil cultivation has had on our rain forests and their inhabitants</a></li>\r\n<li>We will never use plastic, we choose to <span class=\"emphasis\">package our plantbutters in compostable greaseproof paper</span> because this has the lowest environmental impact.  We encourage butter dishes as a way of preserving your butter in the fridge.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>And this is what we intend to implement as soon as we possibly can:</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"ayaList\">\r\n<li>We will be a <a href=\"https://bcorporation.net/\">Certified B Corporation</a>.  Certified B Corporations meet the highest standards of verified social and environmental performance, transparency and accountability. B Corporations are people using business as a force of good.</li>\r\n<li>We will be both <a href=\"https://www.soilassociation.org/\">Soil Association Organic</a> and <a href=\"https://www.vegansociety.com/\">The Vegan Society</a> accredited.</li>\r\n<li>We will use <a href=\"https://www.fairtrade.org.uk/\">Fairtrade Foundation</a> ingredients whenever we can.  Fairtrade is about better prices, decent working conditions, local sustainability and fair terms of trade for farmers and workers in the developing world. It requires companies to pay sustainable prices (which must never fall lower than the market price).</li>\r\n</ul>','Our story','','inherit','closed','closed','','297-revision-v1','','','2018-09-20 16:05:56','2018-09-20 16:05:56','',297,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/297-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(728,1,'2018-09-20 16:30:55','2018-09-20 16:30:55','','aya-product-3','','inherit','open','closed','','aya-product-3-2','','','2018-09-20 16:30:55','2018-09-20 16:30:55','',297,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/aya-product-3.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(729,1,'2018-09-20 16:31:15','2018-09-20 16:31:15','<h1 class=\"visible-xs-block\">Our Story</h1>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"text-center\">\r\n<img src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/aya-product-3.png\" alt=\"aya-product-3\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-728\" />\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>A kinder option</h2>\r\n<p class=\"justify\">The popularity of <span class=\"emphasis\">plantbased</span> foods cannot be denied and the reasons are simple; plantbased foods offer healthier options, have a far lighter tread on the environment and ensure no animal cruelty.  I started Aya because I wanted to offer you the option to choose a purely plantbased alternative to cow\'s butter and other vegetable based oil spreads which is just as tasty and just as versatile - now you can choose a kinder option whenever you like.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote class=\"inline-quote\">\r\n<p class=\"blockquote\">The more we grow and make an impact the more we will be able to make demands that align with our highest values but we will need your loyalty to get there.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<h2>Our values and ethics</h2>\r\nAya is far more than plantbased; our values and ethics extend to everything we do.  As a start:\r\n<ul class=\"ayaList\">\r\n<li>We prioritise <span class=\"emphasis\">sustainability</span> which means that we will always consider the impact of our activities on the the environment:</li>\r\n<li>We prioritise <span class=\"emphasis\">transparency</span> which means we believe that you have a right to know exactly what you are buying and how our business operates:</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>We will always provide you with information about what our products contain, how they are made and where the ingredients are sourced.</li>\r\n<li>We will always warn you of any health risks associated with our products.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li>We prioritise <span class=\"emphasis\">ethical trade</span> and adhere to the Ethical Trade Initiative Basic Code, United Nations Declaration of Human Rights and the International Labour Organisation Core Conventions.</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>We will always provide a fair livelihood for all our employees.  We believe that an individual\'s work should offer in return a sustainable and fair livelihood as well as job satisfaction.  We understand that the role of work is only one aspect of an individual\'s life and that happiness can only be achieved in a holistic and balanced way of living.\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"justify\">As a start-up we realise the importance of creating a profitable business that aligns with our core values.  We must be profitable so that we can pay our employees, provide a comfortable and conducive working environment and pay our investors a fair return on their investment.  Sometimes we may have to make a small compromise on our values but we will always do so with openness and inform you of our decision.  We will then consistently reassess our decisions in a timely manner.</p> \r\n\r\n<h3>This is what we have implemented so far:</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"ayaList\">\r\n<li>We only use <span class=\"emphasis\">non-GMO, organic ingredients</span> because we believe that food should be natural and we do not advocate any chemicals used in the growing, cultivation or processing of our ingredients</li>\r\n<li>We choose <span class=\"emphasis\">no palm-oil</span> because of the <a href=\"https://youtu.be/TQQXstNh45g\">catastrophic effects that palm-oil cultivation has had on our rain forests and their inhabitants</a></li>\r\n<li>We will never use plastic, we choose to <span class=\"emphasis\">package our plantbutters in compostable greaseproof paper</span> because this has the lowest environmental impact.  We encourage butter dishes as a way of preserving your butter in the fridge.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>And this is what we intend to implement as soon as we possibly can:</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"ayaList\">\r\n<li>We will be a <a href=\"https://bcorporation.net/\">Certified B Corporation</a>.  Certified B Corporations meet the highest standards of verified social and environmental performance, transparency and accountability. B Corporations are people using business as a force of good.</li>\r\n<li>We will be both <a href=\"https://www.soilassociation.org/\">Soil Association Organic</a> and <a href=\"https://www.vegansociety.com/\">The Vegan Society</a> accredited.</li>\r\n<li>We will use <a href=\"https://www.fairtrade.org.uk/\">Fairtrade Foundation</a> ingredients whenever we can.  Fairtrade is about better prices, decent working conditions, local sustainability and fair terms of trade for farmers and workers in the developing world. It requires companies to pay sustainable prices (which must never fall lower than the market price).</li>\r\n</ul>','Our story','','inherit','closed','closed','','297-revision-v1','','','2018-09-20 16:31:15','2018-09-20 16:31:15','',297,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/297-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(730,1,'2018-09-20 16:34:39','2018-09-20 16:34:39','','aya-product-1','','inherit','open','closed','','aya-product-1-2','','','2018-09-20 16:34:39','2018-09-20 16:34:39','',287,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/aya-product-1.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(731,1,'2018-09-20 16:34:56','2018-09-20 16:34:56','<h1 class=\"visible-xs-block\">Home</h1>\r\n<p class=\"text-center\">\r\n<img src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/aya-product-1.png\" alt=\"aya-product-1\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-730\" />\r\n</p>\r\n<h2>Simple, honest, clean plantbutters</h2>\r\nOur plantbutters are simple, honest and clean, here\'s how:\r\n<h3>SIMPLE</h3>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\">Our plantbutters were dreamed up in Amy\'s home kitchen using domestic equipment and organic ingredients. Amy\'s motivation was to create a <b>delicious tasting, plantbased alternative to dairy butter</b> because plantbutter <a href=\"http://www.conservationmagazine.org/2014/03/butter-vs-margarine-environmental/\"><b>has a four times lower carbon footprint than dairy butter</b></a> and has no association with animal cruelty often linked to the conventional dairy industry.</p>\r\n<h3>HONEST</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"aya-emphasis-list\">\r\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">SINCERE</span> - We will <b>always provide you with information</b> about what our products contain, how they are made and where the ingredients are sourced.</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">SUSTAINABLE</span> - We are a sustainable business that ensures that all activities related to our business <b>consider the impact it has on the environment</b> and the ability of future generations to meet their own needs.\r\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">CONSCIOUS BUSINESS</span> - We believe that our business should align with your highest values so that <b>when you choose our products you are doing the greatest good for the earth and all its beings</b>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>CLEAN</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"aya-emphasis-list\">\r\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">NO HEXANE</span> - We use only organic ingredients which means our ingredients are <b>grown with natural, organic fertilisers and pesticides and do not undergo any toxic processing</b>. Our plant oils have been extracted without solvents unlike un-organic oils which use Hexane, a petroleum derivative, to extract non-organic oils from their seeds.</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">NO PALM-OIL</span> - We <b>prefer cocoa butter</b> which is naturally firm at room temperature and which gives our plantbutters their unique melt-in-the-mouth quality just like dairy butter.</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">NO GMO</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">NO DAIRY</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">NO GLUTEN</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"emphasis\">NO PLASTIC</span> - We package our plantbutters in <b>compostable packaging</b> and we will never use plastic.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Who is Aya</h2>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\"><b>Aya is a west African Goddess of forests, she protects the forest and its animals and she teaches her tribe how to use the plants to sustain and heal themselves. We chose the name Aya because we align with her values.</b></p>\r\n<p class=\"text-center\">\r\n<img src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/aya-forest.jpg\" alt=\"aya-forest\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-562\" />\r\n</p>\r\n','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','287-revision-v1','','','2018-09-20 16:34:56','2018-09-20 16:34:56','',287,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/287-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(732,1,'2018-09-20 16:44:42','2018-09-20 16:44:42','<p class=\"text-right green\">29th November 2017</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\">I recently attended a competitive 2 day event based around creating an investable business opportunity. I found the whole event quite stressful. My decision to be an active participant meant that from the start I had made myself vulnerable to success or failure. When I was forced to face the rejection of my first pitch it was a very difficult time. I wasn\'t able to stay present, to be in the moment. I found myself creating illusions about how the other participants perceived me, slipping back into old stories of victimhood. It took me a while to find my strength and inner-worth. I kept breathing, pulling myself back to the here and now and thankfully I did recover and focused on helping my team pitch our idea. Unfortunately our idea didn\'t win or come second.</p>\r\n<blockquote class=\"inline-quote\">\r\n<p>We can create a new culture where individuals are inspired to try without fear and the stigma of failure</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\">On the way home at the end of the event I started to think about the differences between success and failure. My understanding of success and failure is that it is based on achieving a goal, an aim or a purpose. In competitive scenarios the successor is the one who comes closest to achieving the goal, aim or purpose. It makes sense then that the first thing we need to do is clearly understand the goal and then ensure that our plan of action is directed at achieving this. I realised that I hadn\'t taken the time to understand the point system that the judges were using to evaluate the winner; I was never going to be successful without this knowledge.</p>\r\n<p class=\"text-center\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-487\" src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/successfailure.jpg\" alt=\"successfailure\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\">We all know that failure is inevitable, it is part of life. Some say that failure is the key to success and perhaps that is true but only in so far as you choose to learn from failure. If failure has you feeling so hurt and disheartened that you decide not to expose yourself and give up then it won\'t help you succeed. With this in mind we must choose our goal, aim or purpose carefully. If we are passionate about achieving our goal, aim or purpose because we know that it will bring us lasting fulfilment, satisfaction and happiness then we are more likely to learn from our failures allowing them to further motivate us to try again.</p>\r\n<p class=\"justify\">Perhaps the biggest difference between success and failure is our response to it. I imagined how my team would have responded if we had been successful. We would have glowed with pride and smiled with accomplishment. We would have praised each other on our efforts, quickly forgetting the difficulties that we had faced. We would have been open to integrating with other participants, taking praise and talking about how and what we had done to achieve our success. And how did we act in failure? We were outwardly sympathetic towards our team members. We were introvert, retrospective, critical and analytical. We wanted to to expose the weeds and acknowledge the areas of weakness. We made comparisons about the validity of our idea compared with those that were successful, keen to discover the key to their success.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote class=\"inline-quote\">\r\n<p>We can glow with pride and smile with accomplishment because we gave it a go, because without those that try, those that are willing to expose themselves and make themselves vulnerable, humanity will not progress</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\">When I think about success and failure they are two sides to the same coin. In both scenarios we have a vision, set a goal, make a plan and execute it. It is only the final outcome that is different. I believe that the best thing we can do to alleviate the suffering we create around failure is to respond to failure as we do in success. If we can fail in the knowledge that we will learn from our mistakes, then we can create a new culture where individuals are inspired to try without fear and the stigma of failure. <span class=\"emphasis\">If in failure we can be equally retrospective and analytical about our strengths and our weaknesses, then we can play a better, stronger hand and we can celebrate our strengths despite failure. And just as importantly, if in success we can maintain humility, if we reject feelings of superiority, grandiosity and importance and if we respond just as we do in failure then we narrow the gap between success and failure, and we highlight the significance and importance of the journey rather than the achievement of a goal.</span></p>','Success is failure turned inside out','','inherit','closed','closed','','463-revision-v1','','','2018-09-20 16:44:42','2018-09-20 16:44:42','',463,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/463-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(733,1,'2018-09-20 16:54:00','2018-09-20 16:54:00','','aya-original','','inherit','open','closed','','aya-original-3','','','2018-09-20 16:54:00','2018-09-20 16:54:00','',607,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/aya-original-1.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(734,1,'2018-09-20 16:54:12','2018-09-20 16:54:12','<h1 class=\"visible-xs-block\">Aya Spreadable</h1>\r\n<p class=\"text-center\">\r\n<img src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/aya-original-1.png\" alt=\"aya-original\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-733\" />\r\n</p>\r\n<h2>Aya Original</h2>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\">Aya Original is our first offering.  We chose Aya Original as our first product because it is the closest <b>organic plantbased alternative to dairy butter</b>.  It\'s <span class=\"emphasis\">creamy</span>, <span class=\"emphasis\">melty</span> and has a <span class=\"emphasis\">delicious, delicate</span> flavour.  We would like everyone to choose Aya Original over dairy butter because plantbutter <a href=\"http://www.conservationmagazine.org/2014/03/butter-vs-margarine-environmental/\"><b>has a four times lower carbon footprint than dairy butter</b></a> and has no association with animal cruelty often linked to the conventional dairy industry.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"blue text-justify\">We encourage you to try Aya on warm toast (so melty and scrummy) and bread (creamy and soft), for cooking (think mushrooms sizzling in plantbutter) or for baking (substitute Aya for butter).</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Ingredients</h3>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\"><span class=\"emphasis\">Organic steamed coconut oil, water, organic steamed cocoa butter, organic cold-pressed safflower oil, Himalayan pink salt , organic sunflower lecithin</span> <b>(vegetable fat spread 71%)</b></p>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\">The coconut oil and cacao butter have been steamed to remove their flavours. Cocoa butter is what gives Aya its melt-in-the-mouth quality, it also helps it stay hard at room temperature. Our safflower oil is <b>cold pressed</b> which is a great way of maintaining its nutritional benefits.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Dietary and lifestyle</h3>\r\n<ul class=\"ayaList\">\r\n 	<li>ORGANIC INGREDIENTS</li>\r\n<li>NO GMO INGREDIENTS</li>\r\n 	<li>NO PALM OIL</li>\r\n 	<li>NO DAIRY OR LACTOSE</li>\r\n<li>No GLUTEN</li>\r\n 	<li>Suitable for VEGANS</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Typical nutritional values per 100g</h3>\r\n<table class=\"table table-striped\"><colgroup> <col /> <col /></colgroup>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Typical values</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Per 100g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Energy (kJ/kCal)</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">2636 / 636</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Total fat</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">71g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Saturated</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">42g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Carbohydrates</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Sugar</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Fibre</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Protein</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">0g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr valign=\"TOP\">\r\n<td width=\"50%\">Salt</td>\r\n<td width=\"50%\">1.34g</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3>Where are Aya Original\'s ingredients from?</h3>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\">We source our organic steamed cocoa butter from <a href=\"https://www.realfoodsource.com/\">RealFoodSource</a> who import the <b>cocoa from Dominican Republic</b>. Our organic steamed coconut oil is from <a href=\"http://www.kerfootgroup.co.uk/\">Kerfoot</a> whose <b>coconut oils originate from Philipines and / or India</b>. Our organic cold-pressed safflower oil is from <a href=\"http://www.meridianfoods.co.uk/\">Meridian</a> whose <b>safflower oil originates from India</b>. We use organic sunflower lecithin to give Aya a creamy and spreadable texture.  Our sunflower lecithin is sourced from <a href=\"https://www.theingredients.co.uk/\">The Ingredients Consultancy</a> whose source <b>sunflower lecithin from a variety of countries (Bulgaria, China, Croatia, France, Germany, India, Italy, Kazakhstan, Netherlands, Austria, Poland, Romania, Russia, Serbia, Slovakia, Slovenia, Spain, Czech Republic, Turkey, Ukraine, Hungary and USA).</b></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>What are the health risks associated with Aya Original?</h3>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\">Aya Original contains <b>10% less overall fat and 9% less saturated fat then cow\'s butter</b>. Aya Original has a <b>total fat content of 71%, of which 42% is saturated fat</b>. Coconut oil and cocoa butter are the main contributors to the saturated fat content. <b>Safflower oil is a healthy fat composed of predominantly poly-unsaturated fat</b>. <span class=\"emphasis\">Aya Original should be consumed responsibly as eating high levels of saturated fat can raise your cholesterol and increase risk of heart disease.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\">Aya Original contains <b>1.5% sunflower lecithin which makes it creamy and spreadable</b>. Our organic sunflower lecithin contains &lt;1g of trans-fat per 100g thus a <span class=\"emphasis\">200g block of Aya contains &lt;0.03g of trans fat</span>.</p>','Aya Original','','inherit','closed','closed','','607-revision-v1','','','2018-09-20 16:54:12','2018-09-20 16:54:12','',607,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/607-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(735,1,'2018-10-07 08:43:57','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2018-10-07 08:43:57','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://blog.calloftheforest.com/?p=735',0,'post','',0),(736,1,'2018-10-07 08:44:35','2018-10-07 08:44:35','<p class=\"text-center\">\r\n<img src=\"http://blog.calloftheforest.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/aya-original-1.png\" alt=\"aya-original\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-733\" />\r\n</p>\r\n<h2>Aya Original</h2>\r\n<p class=\"text-justify\">Aya Original is our first offering.  We chose Aya Original as our first product because it is the closest <b>organic plantbased alternative to dairy butter</b>.  It\'s <span class=\"emphasis\">creamy</span>, <span class=\"emphasis\">melty</span> and has a <span class=\"emphasis\">delicious, delicate</span> flavour.  We would like everyone to choose Aya Original over dairy butter because plantbutter <a href=\"http://www.conservationmagazine.org